## {N}. Navigation

**As a visitor** I want to move between pages using the menu so I can explore the site.

Acceptance Criteria:
- The navigation menu opens from the sidebar and closes again
- The menu lists all the main pages and each link goes to the right URL
- The site logo always returns to the home page
- The menu is usable with a keyboard, including Escape to close it
- Screen readers announce the menu's purpose

## {N+1}. Responsive

**As a mobile visitor** I want every page to be usable on a phone so I can browse on the go.

Acceptance Criteria on phones (≤ 768px):
- Page layouts collapse to a single column where applicable
- Touch targets are large enough to tap reliably
- The mobile menu opens and closes
- No horizontal scrolling

## {N+2}. Metadata / SEO

**As a search crawler** I want clear metadata on every page so I can index and rank the site correctly.

Acceptance Criteria:
- Every page exposes a unique title and description for search engines and link previews
- Every page declares its canonical URL
- The staging site is excluded from search indexes
- Production publishes correct preview metadata for social sharing

## {N+3}. Accessibility

**As a screen-reader user** I want to navigate every page without obstacles so I can use the site independently.

Acceptance Criteria:
- The site follows WCAG 2.1 AA standards for headings, landmarks, alt text, labels, contrast, and keyboard focus
- The Marketplace, Artists, Exhibitions, Contact and About pages pass an automated accessibility scan with no critical violations
- Animations and pre-hydration content respect screen-reader expectations

## {N+4}. Performance

**As a visitor** I want pages to load quickly so I don't bounce before content renders.

Acceptance Criteria (mobile):
- Performance ≥ 70 (target 90)
- Accessibility ≥ 95
- Best Practices ≥ 95
- SEO ≥ 90
- Above-the-fold images load with priority; below-the-fold images lazy-load
- Fonts are preloaded so headings don't shift after page load

## {N+5}. Console / Network Health

**As a developer** I want clean runtime signals so production issues are easy to spot.

Acceptance Criteria:
- The site is free of runtime errors and broken requests on the critical-path pages, verified by automated checks
- Any deprecation warnings are noted and tracked
